Summary In my current role, I do thermal design and analysis work on slim mobile devices. This covers system level as well as individual component level modeling; steady state and transient analysis both are important. I also handle all aspects of using software to "turn down the heat"​ inside passively cooled devices to protect important temperatures, both inside and outside the unit. It involves transient thermal behavior, chip performance, and user experience; thermal modeling, data analysis, and engineering judgement factor into decisions. 

In my consultant life, I got exposure to a wide range of projects. From small heat sinks to large complete electronic systems, I covered thermal and cooling aspects of product development, and made sure thermal considerations were addressed early in the design cycle. I had some LED and also solar projects too. I've also done some manufacturing equipment work -- furnaces, ovens and CVD reactors. 

I especially like the creative process of working out the product architecture, and I really love tackling things I've never done before. I also like sharing my knowledge, and find teaching enjoyable. I've taught a class on my favorite Excel spreadsheet features. 

Specialties: Use thermal analysis to quantify effects of any suggested changes, and identify the most significant; 
Build and instrument experimental thermal models, log and analyze data to determine underlying phenomena; 
Synthesize results from both analysis and physical models to understand system and factor interactions; 
Proactively communicate with system design teams to arrive at practical solutions in the face of uncertainty, complexity, and shifting requirements. Summary In my current role, I do thermal design and analysis work on slim mobile devices. This covers system level as well as individual component level modeling; steady state and transient analysis both are important. I also handle all aspects of using software to "turn down the heat"​ inside passively cooled devices to protect important temperatures, both inside and outside the unit. It involves transient thermal behavior, chip performance, and user experience; thermal modeling, data analysis, and engineering judgement factor into decisions. 

